'My kids had been sick with the flu, rotavirus,' she said. 

'It's been happening for a month. There were things that haven't been taken care of. I feel like I'm getting accused of being a bad mom for worrying about my kids rather than my house.'  

Campbell said the children, ranging in age from 9 months to 13 years, have been placed in the temporary custody of the Department of Social Services.

One of the children did not belong to either suspect. 

Both Poole and Dishner have been released on bond. 

Dishner also was charged on an old driving with a revoked driver's license. 

It was not clear if Dishner and Poole have lawyers. 

